ROLEX PARIS MASTERS
November 3, 2020
Pablo Carreno Busta
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
  P. CARRENO BUSTA/J. Struff
 7-6, 6-2
 THE MODERATOR:   Questions, please.
 Q. You're through now to the third round.  You played two matches back-to-back days.  Can you talk us through your win over Jan-Lennard Struff this evening, what went well for you, why you think you're playing so well this week?
 PABLO CARRENO BUSTA:   Well, after the win yesterday, I didn't have much time to recover, but my confidence was very high today.
 I was serving really good, but I think the key was the first and the second balls after return and after serve.  I think that I played very aggressive these balls, and I make a lot of winners from everywhere.  I'm happy for the victory, because Jan on this surface is a really tough guy.
 Thinking in the third round I have opportunity to be in quarterfinal, so I would like to take advantage of.
 Q. Do you like your chances going forward the rest of this week?
 PABLO CARRENO BUSTA:   Yeah, why not?  I'm playing good.  I'm playing with a lot of confidence now.  And I told you yesterday that probably the last two weeks I didn't feel comfortable on court, I play sometimes good, sometimes bad.  Performance was not very good.
 But yesterday and today I feel really comfortable and that's the important thing.
   
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT